HEADWORD: Recompensation
<hw>Re*com`pen*sa"tion</hw> <pr>(r?*k?m`p?n*s?"sh?n)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[Cf. LL. <ets>recompensatio</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>Recompense.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Scots Law)</fld> <def>Used to denote a case where a
set-off pleaded by the defendant is met by a set-off pleaded by the
plaintiff.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Recompense</ent>⟦br⟧
